we could use your help!\r\n\r\nWe hold our annual memorial event Patty’s Purse Bingo in November to celebrate the life of Patty and others who have suffered through the trial of pancreatic cancer. Our goal is to raise funds in Patty’s name to fight this disease and to increase awareness through positive events that bring caring people together. Please look at our Events page for more information.\r\n\r\nClick here to learn more about Patty, why she\'s so special, and why Patty’s Pals needs YOUR help!','Patty\'s Pals','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2015-05-05 05:43:02','2015-05-05 05:43:02','',8,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/?p=11',0,'revision','',0),(12,1,'2015-05-05 05:44:58','2015-05-05 05:44:58','Patty\'s Pals is a group that came together to assist a special critical care nurse suffering from Stage IV pancreatic cancer, Patty Rojas. Many of us are nurses, some are not; however, all of us shared the common goal of helping our friend and loved one Patty deal with cancer and all the pain it can bring. It occurred to us that, collectively, we had helped thousands of people through all sorts of acute health care crises and now we had a chance to help one of our own.\r\n\r\nAt that time, our goal was to raise funds for Patty through positive events that bring caring people together. Sadly, Patty lost her battle with cancer on November 9, 2011, the day before her youngest child’s second birthday. Although she left us in body, Patty\'s independent and carefree spirit remains with us always. Currently, Patty’s Pals carries on her legacy through a spirited annual event, Patty’s Purse Bingo. Via this happy occasion, we encourage attendees to honor the memory of Patty and other pancreatic cancer sufferers by remembering and celebrating their zest for life. All of the proceeds benefit the Pancreatic Cancer Action Network.','About Patty\'s Pals','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2015-05-05 05:44:58','2015-05-05 05:44:58','',0,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(13,1,'2015-05-05 05:44:58','2015-05-05 05:44:58','Patty\'s Pals is a group that came together to assist a special critical care nurse suffering from Stage IV pancreatic cancer, Patty Rojas. Many of us are nurses, some are not; however, all of us shared the common goal of helping our friend and loved one Patty deal with cancer and all the pain it can bring. It occurred to us that, collectively, we had helped thousands of people through all sorts of acute health care crises and now we had a chance to help one of our own.\r\n\r\nAt that time, our goal was to raise funds for Patty through positive events that bring caring people together. Sadly, Patty lost her battle with cancer on November 9, 2011, the day before her youngest child’s second birthday. Although she left us in body, Patty\'s independent and carefree spirit remains with us always. Currently, Patty’s Pals carries on her legacy through a spirited annual event, Patty’s Purse Bingo. Via this happy occasion, we encourage attendees to honor the memory of Patty and other pancreatic cancer sufferers by remembering and celebrating their zest for life. All of the proceeds benefit the Pancreatic Cancer Action Network.','About Patty\'s Pals','','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-v1','','','2015-05-05 05:44:58','2015-05-05 05:44:58','',12,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/?p=13',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2015-05-05 05:51:24','2015-05-05 05:51:24','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-42 alignright\" src=\"http://pattyspals.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/05055124/pattyisiah.jpg\" alt=\"Patty &amp; Isiah\" width=\"221\" height=\"166\" />Patty was a 43 year old single mother of 4 who was diagnosed in May 2010 with Stage 4 pancreatic cancer with metastasis to the liver. She was a dedicated ICU nurse who cared for thousands of critically ill patients and saved many lives. Patty\'s last nursing role included being a member of the Rapid Response Team, allowing her to put mind, body and soul into the immediate resuscitation efforts of many acute patients. Patty always felt that it was quite ironic that she required others to assist in her care, knowing that this was a place no nurse ever wishes to be. Sadly, but comfortably, Patty died on November 9, 2011, blessing her family and friends with many cherished memories.','About Patty','','publish','closed','closed','','about-patty','','','2015-05-05 22:33:56','2015-05-06 05:33:56','',0,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/?page_id=14',0,'page','',0),(16,1,'2015-05-05 05:51:24','2015-05-05 05:51:24','<img class=\" size-full wp-image-15 alignright\" src=\"http://preview.pattyspals.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/pattyisiah.jpg\" alt=\"Patty &amp; Isiah\" width=\"221\" height=\"166\" />Patty was a 43 year old single mother of 4 who was diagnosed in May 2010 with Stage 4 pancreatic cancer with metastasis to the liver. She was a dedicated ICU nurse who cared for thousands of critically ill patients and saved many lives. Patty\'s last nursing role included being a member of the Rapid Response Team, allowing her to put mind, body and soul into the immediate resuscitation efforts of many acute patients. Patty always felt that it was quite ironic that she required others to assist in her care, knowing that this was a place no nurse ever wishes to be. Sadly, but comfortably, Patty died on November 9, 2011, blessing her family and friends with many cherished memories.','About Patty','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-v1','','','2015-05-05 05:51:24','2015-05-05 05:51:24','',14,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/2015/05/05/14-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2015-05-05 05:55:31','2015-05-05 05:55:31','Patty’s Pals cannot begin to thank all of those who donate time, money, gifts, and most important, their love and caring! Your assistance in keeping Patty\'s memory alive by supporting her wish of increasing pancreatic cancer awareness continues to mean more to family and friends than you will ever know. Thank you from the many hearts that loved and still love Patty.\r\n<div>To donate, please make checks payable to \"Patty\'s Pals\" and mail them to:</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>501 East 3rd Street</div>\r\n<div>Delphos, OH 45833</div></blockquote>\r\nInclude \'donation\' in the memo.','Donate','','publish','closed','closed','','donate','','','2015-05-05 05:55:31','2015-05-05 05:55:31','',0,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(18,1,'2015-05-05 05:55:22','2015-05-05 05:55:22','Patty’s Pals cannot begin to thank all of those who donate time, money, gifts, and most important, their love and caring! Your assistance in keeping Patty\'s memory alive by supporting her wish of increasing pancreatic cancer awareness continues to mean more to family and friends than you will ever know. Thank you from the many hearts that loved and still love Patty.\r\n<div>To donate, please make checks payable to \"Patty\'s Pals\" and mail them to:</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>501 East 3rd Street</div>\r\n<div>Delphos, OH 45833</div></blockquote>\r\nInclude \'donation\' in the memo.','Donate','','inherit','open','open','','17-revision-v1','','','2015-05-05 05:55:22','2015-05-05 05:55:22','',17,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/2015/05/05/17-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2015-05-05 06:03:53','2015-05-05 06:03:53','Email: <a href=\"mailto:pattyspals@gmail.com\">pattyspals@gmail.com</a>\r\n\r\nPhone: 419-296-9911','Contact','','publish','closed','closed','','contact','','','2015-05-05 06:03:53','2015-05-05 06:03:53','',0,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/?page_id=19',0,'page','',0),(20,1,'2015-05-05 06:03:53','2015-05-05 06:03:53','Email: <a href=\"mailto:pattyspals@gmail.com\">pattyspals@gmail.com</a>\r\n\r\nPhone: 419-296-9911','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-v1','','','2015-05-05 06:03:53','2015-05-05 06:03:53','',19,'http://preview.pattyspals.com/2015/05/05/19-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2015-05-05 06:05:26'